NY Central RR engine 1528 was apparently built in June 1890 by the Rogers Locomotive and Machine Works of Paterson, New Jersey. 

According to Wikipedia: Rogers &quot;built more than six thousand steam locomotives for railroads around the world...Rogers was the second-most popular American locomotive manufacturer of the 19th century behind the Baldwin Locomotive Works amongst almost a hundred manufacturers.&quot; 

No Rogers 2-6-0 engines have survived.
